Barclays, Computacenter, Stratex: U.K., Irish Equity Preview

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-07-12T06:46:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-11/bank-of-ireland-barclays-stratex-u-k-irish-equity-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
that may have unusual share-price changes in U.K. and Irish
markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses and prices are from
the last market close.  Futures on the benchmark FTSE 100 Index slumped 0.9 percent
to 5,840 at 7:43 a.m. in London. The FTSE 100 plunged 61.42, or
1 percent, to 5,929.16 yesterday. The FTSE All-Share Index
dropped 1.1 percent to 3,088.28, while Ireland’s ISEQ Index
retreated 1.5 percent to 2,900.25.  Barclays Plc (BARC)  :  The lender’s call-options volume
jumped to the highest since February in the U.S. as investors
bet that the second-largest U.K. bank by assets will rebound
from a two-year low. European authorities will release stress-
test results for the region’s lenders on July 15. The stock
slumped 3.8 percent to 234 pence.  Computacenter Plc (CCC)  : The distributed IT services
company said first-half profitability will be “comfortably
ahead” of the same period a year earlier. Computacenter also
said that trading is “in line” with full-year forecasts. The
shares fell 1.7 percent to 460 pence.  Premier Oil Plc (PMO)  : The U.K.-based oil explorer said
production this year may be less than forecast after an
unplanned shutdown at the Balmoral field in the  North Sea .
Production will average 40,000 to 45,000 barrels a day, compared
with a previous estimate of 45,000 barrels a day. The shares
fell 1.9 percent to 434.8 pence.  Royal Bank of Scotland Group Plc (RBS)  : Wells Fargo &
Co. and RBS will sell $1.48 billion in bonds backed by
commercial mortgages, according to people with knowledge of the
sales. The shares slumped 4 percent to 35.7 pence.  Stratex International Plc (STI LN): The London-based mining
company called Centamin Egypt Ltd.’s offer to acquire Stratex’s
joint-venture partner Sheba Exploration U.K. Plc a “welcome
development.” The stock rose 1.2 percent to 8.3 pence.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in  London  at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
